other_tests.findings: Total testosterone (505 ng/dL; reference range, 270-1100 ng/dL) and free testosterone (1.0 ng/dL; reference range, 1.5-3.5 ng/dL) were measured.
No prostate biopsy was performed; it was suggested for men with elevated PSA or abnormal DRE findings prior to testosterone replacement.
Prostate examination revealed a smooth firm prostate that was minimally enlarged without nodules.
